cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM. 

This paper deals with the task of editing text in natural images, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The proposed end-to-end trainable style retention network (SRNet) also involves machine learning (ML) techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses various real-world applications such as text image synthesis, augmented reality (AR) translation, and information hiding, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
